description:
Subscribe to real-time component events. This enables reactive AI that responds to user interactions automatically.

You can subscribe to:
- selection_change: When user selects rows, cells, items
- filter_change: When user applies filters
- data_update: When component data changes
- action_triggered: When user clicks actions
- suggest_component: When components suggest related components
- custom: Custom events from components

Use this to build reactive experiences that feel magical to users.

IMPORTANT: Subscriptions persist across messages. Use sparingly for critical events only.

** EXAMPLES **

1. Subscribe to table selection changes:
{
  "events": ["selection_change"],
  "componentId": "table-1"
}

2. Subscribe to all filter changes:
{
  "events": ["filter_change", "data_update"]
}

3. Auto-respond to selection changes:
{
  "events": ["selection_change"],
  "componentId": "table-1",
  "autoRespond": {
    "selection_change": {
      "action": "Show details of selected rows in sidebar"
    }
  }
}
